   2. At low flow, no stream was acidic, alkalinity being greater than or equal to 29 mueq L-1 and pH greater than or equal to6.4. However, NO3- was present in streamwater at these flows in concentrations that suggested anthropogenic enrichment, and its concentration correlated with spatial patterns of N deposition from the atmosphere.
